<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> rdfs:label "Secondary Source: Broughton MRR I" ;
	a dprr:SecondarySource ;
	dprr:hasName "The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. I" ;
	dprr:hasBiblio "Broughton, T. R. S., The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. I. Published by the American Philological Association. New York 1952." ;
	dprr:hasAbbreviation "Broughton MRR I" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PrimarySourceReference/208> rdfs:label "Primary Source Reference: #208" ;
	a dprr:PrimarySourceReference ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. ad Q. fr. I 1.10" ;
	dprr:forAssertion <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/204> .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7594> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7594" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. pl. 470. See MRR 1.31. Note that J.-C. Richard, Origines de la plebe romaine 529, prefers Sicinius, the reading of Diodorus and the properly plebeian name; cf. Ogilvie, Comm. Liv. 382. See T. Sicinius (13). Cos. 487.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/164> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #164" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Diod. (11.68.7) and Piso (in Liv. 2.58.2) agree on four names to which Piso adds Mecilius as a fifth. Duillius and Siccius prosecuted Ap. Claudius, Consul 471, who died before the proceedings ended (Liv. 2.61.1-9; Dion. Hal. 9.52.1-54.6). Note, however that according to Fast. Cap. he became Consul in 451 and Decemvir in 451 and 450." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/163> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #163" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "C. Sicinius in Diod. almost certainly refers to the same person as Livy's Siccius. See 493, Tribunes of the Plebs." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/204> rdfs:label "Post Assertion: #204" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertion ;
	dprr:isAboutPerson <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/Person/120> ;
